[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Mark 15:2-5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Mark 15:2-5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Pilate asked him, Art thou the king of the Jews? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— These verses are explained in the notes on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 27:11-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But Jesus yet answered nothing ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— This is not an accurate translation of the original, (which is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ουκετι ουδεν απεκριθη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) implying, as Dr. Campbell justly observes, “that he had answered nothing to the former question, the reverse of which is the fact, as appears, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 15:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". All the Latin translators say rightly, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Nihil amplius respondit, he answered nothing more, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or what is manifestly equivalent. All the foreign translations give the same sense. Yet, to show how difficult it is to preserve a uniform attention, and how liable at times even judicious persons are to run blindfold into the errors of their predecessors; it may be observed, that Wesley is the only modern translator who has escaped a blunder not more repugnant to the fact, as recorded in the verses immediately preceding, than contradictory to the import of the Greek expression here used. His version is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Answered nothing any more. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The rest without exception say, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Still answered nothing, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or words to that purpose. Yet, in the translation commonly used in Queen Elizabeth’s reign, the sense was truly exhibited, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Answered no more at all.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
